    "image_text": "<div class='blocktext'>While dam managers have been able to sufficiently release water from the lake, through the damaged main spillway, they worry that future runoff could test their success. Snowpack in the mountains is near record highs, and as it melts this spring, the lake’s inflow is likely to be large. Most reservoirs in California are similarly at or near capacity and are releasing large amounts of water downstream.</div>"
